Romney Trailed by Trump, Huckabee in Republican Poll, WSJ Says

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-04-06T21:22:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/romney-trailed-by-trump-huckabee-in-republican-poll-wsj-says.html
Former Massachusetts Governor Mitt
Romney led a poll of Republican primary votes for their
nomination for president, the Wall Street Journal reported,
citing a WSJ/NBC poll.  Real estate investor  Donald Trump  and former Arkansas
Governor  Mike Huckabee  were tied in second place, the newspaper
said. Romney was favored by 21 percent those polled while Trump
and Huckabee each had the support of 17 percent, the newspaper
said on its website.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  